narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: By taking this course, my reading, writing, listening, and speaking skills improved to an intermediate level. We learned how to communicate through these four areas with more complex sentence structures and to be more intentional with our sentence constructions in order to create more meaning.
I developed better understanding of grammar, idioms, and speaking.
I greatly developed my Korean grammar and storytelling skills.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Everything about this course is a strength! I really appreciate Professor Lee-Smith's project-based learning approach because it pushes us to apply what we know and to be able to recall what we've learned and apply it to everyday concepts.
I like the creativity-focused projects, but I wish there were tests/grammar drills.

This course is designed so that we get a lot of feedback on speaking every day and writing every week.  It is focused so that we can build our presentational speaking skills.  There are really no weaknesses.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would! This course will take your elementary Korean abilities to the next level.
I would, but only to a super self-motivated student who wouldn't need a test as an excuse to learn grammar and vocabulary.
Yes.  It is intensive since class meets every day for 3 hours but it is absolutely worth it.  Your Korean will improve.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
